{"title_page": "List of Bull (2016 TV series) episodes", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n{{DISPLAYTITLE:List of ''Bull'' (2016 TV series) episodes}}\n''[[Bull (2016 TV series)|Bull]]'' is an American drama television series starring [[Michael Weatherly]]. CBS ordered the program to series on May 13, 2016,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2016/05/training-day-bull-macgyver-the-great-indoors-matt-leblanc-jason-katims-cbs-series-1201755376/|title='Training Day', 'Bull', 'MacGyver', 'The Great Indoors', Matt LeBlanc Comedy & Jason Katims Drama Picked Up By CBS|last=Andreeva|first=Nellie|website=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=May 13, 2016|accessdate=May 13, 2016}}</ref> and it premiered on September 20, 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2016/06/cbs-fall-premiere-dates-2016-1201776569/|title=CBS Sets Fall 2016 Premiere Dates, Slates JonBenet Ramsey Limited Series|last=Andreeva|first=Nellie|website=Deadline Hollywood|date=June 21, 2016|accessdate=June 21, 2016}}</ref> The show is based on the early days of talk show host [[Phil McGraw|Dr. Phil McGraw]]'s career, when he was a trial consultant.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tvline.com/2016/03/16/michael-weatherly-dr-phil-bull-cbs-drama-series-pilot-cast/|title=''NCIS'' Michael Weatherly to Play Dr. Phil in CBS Drama Pilot ''Bull''|last=Ausiello|first=Michael|website=[[TVLine]]|date=March 16, 2016|accessdate=October 8, 2016}}</ref> On May 9, 2019, CBS renewed the series for a fourth season.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/05/bull-renewed-season-4-cbs-michael-weatherly-1202604917/|title='Bull' Renewed For Season 4 By CBS|work=Deadline Hollywood|last1=Andreeva|first1=Nellie|last2=Petski|first2=Denise|date=May 9, 2019|accessdate=May 9, 2019}}</ref>\n\n{{Aired episodes|2020|4|6|showpage=Bull (2016 TV series)|title=Bull|finished=}}\n\n==Series overview==\n<onlyinclude>{{Series overview\n| infoA      = Rank\n| infoB      = Average viewership<br />(in millions)\n\n| color1     = #